I must've done something wrong. Usually, results in my kitchen are in line with the previous reviews. I have a great oven, followed the recipe to the letter - almost - and mine came out totally underbaked. Toothpick came out clean, topped looked browned and mostly done, but I thought it didn't look quite set. I knew I was right when I went to 'turn it out' on rack (more like 'dump it out'). Instead of raisins I used dried cranberries. Could this be the reason for the goopy mess? It all sounded so good...and looked good on the outside. Maybe I'll give it another try.

